Simple assertions and measurements made about a patient, device or other subject
Observations are a key aspect of healthcare. This resource is used to capture those that do not require more sophisticated mechanisms.
Used for "simple" observations such as vital signs, height, weight, smoking status, comments, etc. *Not* used for lab results, diagnostic images or other more complex observations.
Observation[isNormalAct() and subsumesCode("ActClass#OBS", classCode) and moodCode="EVN" and domainMember("SimpleObservationType", code)]

Allows observations to be distinguished and referenced

Knowing what kind of observation is being made is essential to understanding the observation.
Indicates where on the subject's body the observation was made.
Knowing where observation is made is important for tracking if multiple sites are possible.

The time or time-period the observed value is asserted as being true

The thing the observation is being made about
